ecting the region’s racial diversity, it profiles not only white drag kings, but also those who are African American, multiracial, and Hispanic. Queer scholar Baker A. Rogers—who has also performed as drag king Macon Love—takes you on an insider’s tour of Southern drag king culture, exploring its history, the communal bonds that unite it, and the controversies that have divided it. King of Hearts offers a groundbreaking look at a subculture that presents a subversion of gender norms while also providing a vital lifeline for non-gender-conforming Southerners.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDrag kingszSouthern StatesxHistory. 0aGender expressionzSouthern States. 0aMale impersonatorszSouthern StatesxHistory. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  adrag kings, LGTBQ, gender, gender studies, women, men, female impersonators, male impersonators, cis women, trans men, non-binary, masculine, personas, Drag Queens, drag, drag performers, American south, southern flair, racial diversity, race, multiracial, queer, drag communities, subculture, gender non-conforming, history of drag, drag king community.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882057940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978820579423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978820579/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK 